# Line endings.
#
# Git for Windows defaults to `core.autocrlf=true`, which rewrites LF to CRLF on checkout.
# A shell script with CRLF line endings dies before it runs a single command:
#
#     bash: ./bin/setup.sh: /usr/bin/env: bad interpreter: No such file or directory
#
# The pre-commit hook fails the same way — and a hook that cannot start is a secret guard
# that is not there. Nail every executable text file to LF, on every platform.

* text=auto

*.sh          text eol=lf
*.py          text eol=lf
.githooks/*   text eol=lf
*.bat         text eol=crlf
*.ps1         text eol=crlf

# Reviewed by a human, edited on GitHub's web editor, read by a Java loader.
# Keep it LF so a Windows edit doesn't rewrite every line in the diff.
*.tsv         text eol=lf

*.jar         binary
*.png         binary
*.jpg         binary
*.docx        binary
